<html><head><title>Devs Ask for Hot Zone Suggestions</title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>Devs Ask for Hot Zone Suggestions</h3><p>Help decide where the next hot zones (extra experience bonus zones) should be!<br><br>Dev Elidroth has started a <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/posts/list.m?topic_id=126034" target="_new">thread</a> for player input.<br><br>Here are the criteria:<br><br>"Nodyin and I are putting together the new Hot Zone list and I'm looking for your input on where they should be. Ideally they should fall into this criteria:<br><br>Hasn't been a Hot Zone in quite awhile (or ever). This is the tough one. It's VERY easy to repeat old choices.<br><br>Is not a keyed zone restricting access for any reason other than level.<br><br>Can be outdoors or indoors.<br><br>Is NOT an LDoN instance (the difficulty with this is just insane for reasons I'd rather not go into right now)."<br><br>So go have your say!</div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Tuesday, 8 Jan, 2008<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=36930">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=36930</a><br>Printed On: Sun Aug 21 9:04:34 PDT 2011<br>©2008 IGN Entertainment</font></span>